solutions.content:
**Problem**: 
We have to return a vector containing cells from range x to y. For this, we would need to iterate from column col1 to col2 and for each iteration, iterate over rows from row1 to row2 (all inclusive).

**Approach**:
We know that the string given to us in the format: [col1][row1]:[col2][row2]
so, s[0] will contain the value col1, s[1] will contain row1, s[2] would be a colon(:), s[3] will contain col2, and s[4] will contain row2.
So, we need to run an iteration from s[0] till s[3]. And for each iteration, iterate from s[1] to s[4], and hence, add values in the format: [column][row] to a string and insert the string to the vector.

**Solution**:

```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<string> cellsInRange(string s) {
        vector<string> ans; //vector in which we would store our result
        for(char column=s[0];column<=s[3];column++) //iterating over columns from col1 to col2
        {
            for(int row=s[1]-'0';row<=s[4]-'0';row++) //iterating over rows from row1 to row2
            {
                string current=""; // we take an empty string for the cell
                current+=column; // add the column to the string
                current+=to_string(row); // add the row number in form of string to the string
                ans.push_back(current); // push the string to the vector
            }
        }
        return ans; // return the vector
    }
};
```

