# Approach

Get time difference between both times and use Greedy Approach (i.e first 60min, then 15min, 5min and 1min). 

The time difference is (minCorr ~ minNow) if correct min is more than current min. (i.e the acute angle in the clock)

But in the other case, it should be the obtuse angle so, the difference is 60 - (minCorr ~ minNow). Further, in this case the hour isn't complete yet so we decrease hour count by 1.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int convertTime(string current, string correct) {
        int hN = (current[0] - '0')*10 + (current[1] - '0')*1;
        int hC = (correct[0] - '0')*10 + (correct[1] - '0')*1;
        int mN = (current[3] - '0')*10 + (current[4] - '0')*1;
        int mC = (correct[3] - '0')*10 + (correct[4] - '0')*1;

        int res = abs(hN - hC);
        int diff{};
        if(mN > mC){
            diff = abs(60- (mN-mC));
            res--;
        }
        else{
            diff = abs(mN - mC);
        }

        while(diff){
            if(diff >=15){
                res++;
                diff -= 15;
            }
            else if(diff >=5){
                res++;
                diff -= 5;
            }
            else{
                res += diff;
                diff = 0;
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```

