## Explanation:

### Solution 01

- Here in the map we’re storing all the tasks count of the same difficulty level.
- Iterating over map and checking 3 conditions:
    - `if(temp < 2)` here we can’t perform the task as the minimum required task needed to do in a single day is 2 → ***return -1.***
    - `if(temp == 2)` here only one day is needed to do the work, so increase 1 in our ans.
    - `if(temp >= 3)` here we’ve more than 2 tasks, so we’ll divide the task number by 3 & add it, even if we have more tasks to do that will be less than 3, so we’ll increase ans value by 1.
- Return ans.
- **Time complexity:** O(n).

---

## Code:

```cpp
//Solution 01:
class Solution {
public:
    int minimumRounds(vector<int>& tasks) {
        unordered_map<int, int> mp;
        int ans = 0;

        for(auto x:tasks){
            mp[x] += 1;
        }

        for(auto x:mp){
            int temp = x.second;
            if(temp < 2) return -1;
            else if(temp == 2) ans++;
            else if(temp >= 3){
                ans += temp/3;
                if(temp%3 != 0) ans++;
            }
        }

        return ans;

    }
};
```

