# Intuition
- We want to cover all the tasks in the lot of 2 or 3.
- To achieve that, we will store the frequency of tasks.
- If the frequency is 1, we will directly return -1. Bcz mp[it]<2 or mp[it]<3.
- If the frequency of any task is exactly 2 or 3. Take it as one round.
- Now the question arises, if the frequency is greater than 2 or 3.
-> We will try to cover all the tasks, which we can cover in the lot of 3.
-> And then for remaining tasks, we cover under lot of 2. 

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minimumRounds(vector<int>& tasks) {
        // store the frequencies 
        map<int,int> mp;
        for( auto &it : tasks ) mp[it]++;

        int rounds = 0;

        for( auto &it : mp ){
            // tasks = [2,3,3]
            if( it.second == 1 ) return -1;
            // tasks = [2,2,3,3,2]
            else if( it.second == 2 || it.second == 3 ) rounds++;

            // tasks = [4,4,4,4,4]
            else if ( it.second>3 ){
                int rem = it.second%3;
                // multiple of 3 
                rounds += it.second/3;
                // multiple of 2 
                if( rem%2 == 0 ) rounds += rem/2;
                // For tasks = [4,4,4,4], rem == 1;
                else rounds += 1;
            }
        }

        return rounds;
    }
};
```

