We will keep the frequency (f) of each level in a map.
If ```f == 1```, we can only complete either 2 or 3 tasks of the same level. Hence, no solution possible.

If ```f % 3 == 0```, then we can complete 3 tasks in every round which will be equal to ```f/3```.
If ```f % 3 != 0```, then number of rounds will always be ```f/3 + 1```.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
*O(n)*

- Space complexity:
*O(n)*

