# Approach
Please upvote

Each time we can choose only one difficulty level.
Lets say difficulty level X appeared K times. 
We need to take M rounds to finish X task which appeared K times.
In each of the M rounds, we can take either 2 or 3 totalling K.
So, 
K=2x+3y where x+y=M
In x rounds we collect 2 tasks, in y rounds we collect 3 tasks. Total we collect K tasks of a particular level. 

Solution: We will precompute the least number of rounds required to complete K tasks regardless of the difficulty level.

Each difficulty level can come in the range 1-10^5
If it comes only once, we cant collect the task since we can collect only 2 at a time or 3 at a time. So if a task comes only once, we return -1.

Dp definition:
dp[i]= least numbe of rounds required to collect a tasks of a particular difficulty level that appeard i times

The base conditions are:
dp[1]=-1
dp[2]=1
dp[3]=1
dp[4]=2

DP expression:
for(i=5 to 10^5)
dp[i]= Math.min(dp[i-2],dp[i-3])+1;
We take minimum of number of rounds required to collect i-2 tasks and number of rounds rquired to collect i-3 tasks. Then we add 1 which is collecting the left over 2 or 3 tasks respectively. 

Summary:
1) Precompute least number of rounds required for any tasks which comes K times (k ranging from 1 to 10^5)
2) Use a hashmap <Task_difficulty, number_of_times_it_appeared> 
3) Iterate over hashmap
    3.1) get the value for each Entry which denotes the count
    3.2) get the least number of rounds required for the value from the dp 
    3.3) add it to the answer
    3.4) return -1 if count is 1
4) return ans




# Complexity
- Time complexity:
N-> for calculating dp array
N-> for iterating to create the hashmap
N-> for iterating over hashmap to calculate answer
O(n)

- Space complexity:
N-> for HashMap
N-> for DP array
O(n)

