<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
If the number of tasks with the same difficulty level exceeds one, there must be one valid result for those tasks.Otherwise, return -1.

By analysing the conditions, all tasks can be solved by taking three tasks at a time, and if the task is less than 3 (which means 2), it can also be done.
So divide the number of tasks (same difference) by three, and add one if the remainder is 2 for all difficulty levels. Finally, return the answer.

