3. we have a remainder 1.(like 7,10,13...)  we need to scarifice one 3 to make allocation for 2. 
         suppose we have 7 which greedly goes as (3+3+1) . to write this interms of 2's and 3's we need to scarifice one 3.  {7= 3+2+2}. so when the reaminder is 1 we need to increse count with ((freq/3) -1 +2) = (freq/3  + 1 ). 

